Day 4: HTML Tables

Tables are used to display data in rows and columns.

Examples:

Employee List
Student Records
Product Details
Reports and Dashboards
1. Basic Table Structure
<table border="1">
    <tr>
        <th>ID</th>
        <th>Name</th>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>1</td>
        <td>Priyadharshini</td>
    </tr>
</table>

Output:

ID	Name
1	Priyadharshini
2. Important Table Tags
Tag	Purpose
table	Creates table
tr	Table row
th	Table header
td	Table data
3. Multiple Rows
<table border="1">

    <tr>
        <th>ID</th>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Role</th>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>1</td>
        <td>Priya</td>
        <td>Java Developer</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>2</td>
        <td>Ram</td>
        <td>Tester</td>
    </tr>

</table>
4. Table Sections
thead

Header section.

tbody

Data section.

<table border="1">

    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>ID</th>
            <th>Name</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>

    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>1</td>
            <td>Priya</td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
            <td>2</td>
            <td>Ram</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>

</table>
5. colspan

Merge columns.

<table border="1">

    <tr>
        <th colspan="2">
            Employee Information
        </th>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>Name</td>
        <td>Priya</td>
    </tr>

</table>
6. rowspan

Merge rows.

<table border="1">

    <tr>
        <td rowspan="2">Java</td>
        <td>Spring Boot</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
        <td>Hibernate</td>
    </tr>

</table>

Interview Questions
1. What is the difference between <th> and <td>?

Answer:

<th> is used for table headers, while <td> is used for table data cells.

2. What is the purpose of <tr>?

Answer:

<tr> defines a table row.

3. What is colspan?

Answer:

colspan is used to merge multiple columns into a single cell.

Example:

<th colspan="2">Employee Details</th>
4. What is rowspan?

Answer:

rowspan is used to merge multiple rows into a single cell.

Example:

<td rowspan="2">Java</td>
5. Why use thead and tbody?

Answer:

They organize table data into header and body sections, making the table more readable and maintainable.

